#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Pregled"

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is it?"
msgstr "Kaj je to?"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KGeoTag is a Free/Libre Open Source photo geotagging program. It's written "
"in C++/<ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">Qt</ulink> and uses the <ulink url="
"\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/\">KDE Frameworks</ulink>. It's published "
"under the terms of the <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/#GPL\">GNU "
"General Public License (GPL)</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"KGeoTag je prosti/brezplačen odprtokodni program za geografsko označevanje "
"fotografij. Napisan je v C++/<ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">Qt</ulink> in "
"uporablja <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/\">KDE Frameworks</"
"ulink>. Objavljeno je pod pogoji <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/"
"#GPL\">Splošne javne licence GNU (GPL)</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is \"Geotagging\"?"
msgstr "Kaj je \"Geo-označevanje (Geotagging)\"?"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Photos (&eg; JPEG images) contain metadata like the creation date, camera "
"information &etc; Those are either stored in the so-called <ulink url="
"\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exif\">Exif header</ulink>, in an <ulink url="
"\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extensible_Metadata_Platform\">XMP sidecar "
"file</ulink> or in both. This data can also represent geographic coordinates "
"so that it's replicable where the images were taken."
msgstr ""
"Fotografije (&eg; slike JPEG) vsebujejo metapodatke, kot so datum "
"ustvarjanja, podatki o fotoaparatu &etc;. Ti so bodisi shranjeni v tako "
"imenovani <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exif\">glavi Exif</"
"ulink> v <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia .org/wiki/"
"Extensible_Metadata_Platform\">priklopni datoteki XMP</ulink> ali v obeh. Ti "
"podatki lahko predstavljajo tudi geografske koordinate, tako da jih je "
"mogoče ponoviti, kje so bile slike posnete."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most cameras don't have GPS receivers, so, most can't save coordinates when "
"taking images. A common approach is to &eg; carry a small GPS logging device "
"along (or nowadays also using a smartphone ;-)), which records a track all "
"the time. Later on, the images' dates can be compared to the GPS log's "
"points' dates to figure out where an image was taken."
msgstr ""
"Večina fotoaparatov nima sprejemnikov GPS, zato večina ne more shraniti "
"koordinat pri fotografiranju. Običajni pristop je &eg; s seboj nosite majhno "
"napravo za beleženje GPS (ali dandanes tudi s pametnim telefonom ;-)), ki "
"ves čas beleži pot. Kasneje lahko datume slik primerjate z datumi točk v "
"dnevniku GPS, da ugotovite, kje je bila slika posneta."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If one knows for sure where the respective photo was taken, it's also "
"possible to assign coordinates to the images manually."
msgstr ""
"Če zagotovo vemo, kje je bila posamezna fotografija posneta, je možno slikam "
"tudi ročno dodeliti koordinate."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "Geotagging with KGeoTag"
msgstr "Geooznačevanje s KGeoTag"

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported file formats"
msgstr "Podprti formati datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KGeoTag currently supports The following image formats: <ulink url=\"https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JPEG\">JPEG</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Portable_Network_Graphics\">PNG</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/WebP\">WebP</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/TIFF\">TIFF</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"OpenRaster\">OpenRaster</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Krita\">Krita Document</ulink>, as well as some TIFF-based RAW image "
"formats: <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raw_image_format\">Canon "
"Raw v2</ulink> (.cr2), <ulink url=\"https://www.nikonusa.com/en/learn-and-"
"explore/a/products-and-innovation/nikon-electronic-format-nef.html\">Nikon "
"Electronic Format</ulink> (.nef) and <ulink url=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/"
"camera-raw/digital-negative.html\">Adobe Digital Negative</ulink> (.dng)."
msgstr ""
"KGeoTag trenutno podpira naslednje formate slik: <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/JPEG\">JPEG</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki /Portable_Network_Graphics\">PNG</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/WebP\">WebP</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org /wiki/TIFF\">TIFF</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"OpenRaster\">OpenRaster</ulink> in <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia .org/"
"wiki/Krita\">Krita Document</ulink>, pa tudi nekatere oblike zapisa slik "
"RAW, ki temeljijo na TIFF: <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Raw_image_format\">Canon Raw v2</ulink> (.cr2), <ulink url=\"https://www."
"nikonusa.com/en/learn-and-explore/a/products-and-innovation/nikon-electronic-"
"format-nef.html\"> Nikon Electronic Format</ulink> (.nef) in <ulink url="
"\"https://helpx.adobe.com/camera-raw/digital-negative.html\">Adobe Digital "
"Negative</ulink> (.dng)."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Geodata can be loaded from (uncompressed) <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/GPS_Exchange_Format\">GPX</ulink> files."
msgstr ""
"Geopodatke je mogoče naložiti iz (nestisnjenih) datotek <ulink url=\"https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GPS_Exchange_Format\">GPX</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assigning images"
msgstr "Dodeljevanje slik"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "KGeoTag offers multiple ways to assign coordinates to images:"
msgstr "KGeoTag ponuja več načinov dodeljevanja koordinat slikam:"

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic tagging"
msgstr "Samodejno označevanje"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most convenient approach is automatic matching using geodata provided by "
"GPX files. Those can be loaded and displayed on a map. Using this data, "
"images can be assigned with matching geographic coordinates by finding (more "
"or less) exact chronological matches, or by interpolating a likely position "
"if no exact match can be found."
msgstr ""
"Najudobnejši pristop je samodejno ujemanje z uporabo geopodatkov, ki jih "
"zagotavljajo datoteke GPX. Te je mogoče naložiti in prikazati na zemljevidu. "
"Z uporabo teh podatkov je mogoče slikam dodeliti ujemajoče se geografske "
"koordinate z iskanjem (bolj ali manj) natančnih kronoloških ujemanj ali z "
"interpolacijo verjetnega položaja, če natančnega ujemanja ni mogoče najti."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normally, the images only provide a time and date, but no timezone. Thus we "
"need to set one to make an assignment possible. The presumably correct "
"timezone is detected from the geographic location of the GPX file, but it "
"can also be set manually."
msgstr ""
"Običajno slike vsebujejo samo čas in datum, ne pa tudi časovnega pasu. Zato "
"ga moramo nastaviti, da omogočimo dodelitev. Domnevno pravilen časovni pas "
"je zaznan iz geografske lokacije datoteke GPX, vendar ga je mogoče nastaviti "
"tudi ročno."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If altitude values aren't set in the dataset or they are not accurate "
"enough, they can be looked up using opentopodata.org (see below)."
msgstr ""
"Če vrednosti nadmorske višine niso nastavljene v naboru podatkov ali niso "
"dovolj natančne, jih je mogoče poiskati s pomočjo opentopodata.org (glejte "
"spodaj)."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The clocks of cameras mostly aren't radio-controlled and often have a slight "
"offset. If the images' dates have a time drift due to the camera's clock "
"being not exactly in sync with the GPS data (which is assumed to be "
"correct), a deviation can be defined. It then will be considered when "
"searching for matches, and can also be used to fix the images' dates."
msgstr ""
"Ure kamer večinoma niso radijsko vodene in imajo pogosto majhen zamik. Če "
"imajo datumi slik časovni zamik zaradi tega, ker ura fotoaparata ni natančno "
"sinhronizirana s podatki GPS (kar se domneva, da so pravilni), je mogoče "
"določiti odstopanje. Nato se bo upoštevalo pri iskanju ujemanj, lahko pa se "
"uporabi tudi za popravljanje datumov slik."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drag and drop interface"
msgstr "Vmesnik povleci in spusti"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another option is tagging images via drag and drop. One or more images can "
"be selected and dropped onto the map, to their respective location (possibly "
"also guided by some GPX track). Elevations can't be ascertained this way, so "
"either, they are left to be \"0 m\" (sea level), entered manually or looked "
"up via opentopodata.org (either automatically or manually, see below)."
msgstr ""
"Druga možnost je označevanje slik z povleci in spusti. Izberete lahko eno "
"ali več slik in jih spustite na zemljevid, na njihovo ustrezno lokacijo "
"(možno tudi vodeno s kakšno sledjo GPX). Nadmorske višine ni mogoče "
"ugotoviti na ta način, zato ostanejo \"0 m\" (morska gladina), vnesene ročno "
"ali poiskane prek opentopodata.org (bodisi samodejno ali ročno, glejte "
"spodaj)."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assigning images to bookmarks"
msgstr "Dodeljevanje slik zaznamkom"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For places frequently assigned to images (like one's home, where one doesn't "
"carry a GPS logger), bookmarks can be defined. Images can then be assigned "
"to the respective coordinates easily."
msgstr ""
"Za mesta, ki so pogosto dodeljena slikam (na primer doma, kjer nimate "
"zapisovalnika GPS), je mogoče določiti zaznamke. Slike lahko nato preprosto "
"dodelite ustreznim koordinatam."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manual assignment"
msgstr "Ročna dodelitev"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It's also possible to enter coordinates for one or more images by hand. The "
"altitudes can be either looked up automatically using opentopodata.org (see "
"below), or also be entered manually."
msgstr ""
"Možno je tudi ročno vnesti koordinate za eno ali več slik. Nadmorske višine "
"je mogoče samodejno poiskati z uporabo opentopodata.org (glejte spodaj) ali "
"pa jih vnesite ročno."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting or looking up elevation information"
msgstr "Nastavitev ali iskanje informacij o višini"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Altitudes can always be set manually. Alternatively, the altitudes can also "
"be looked up querying different elevation datasets using <ulink url="
"\"https://www.opentopodata.org/\">opentopodata.org</ulink>'s API."
msgstr ""
"Nadmorske višine lahko vedno nastavite ročno. Druga možnost je, da nadmorske "
"višine poiščete tudi s poizvedovanjem po različnih naborih podatkov o "
"nadmorski višini z uporabo API-ja <ulink url=\"https://www.opentopodata.org/"
"\">opentopodata.org</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preset is to use the <ulink url=\"https://asterweb.jpl.nasa.gov/gdem.asp"
"\">ASTER</ulink> dataset. This one covers the whole globe. Others can be "
"used as well, cf. <ulink url=\"https://www.opentopodata.org/#public-api"
"\">opentopodata.org's homepage</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Prednastavljena je uporaba nabora podatkov <ulink url=\"https://asterweb.jpl."
"nasa.gov/gdem.asp\">ASTER</ulink>. Ta pokriva ves svet. Uporabimo lahko tudi "
"druge, prim. <ulink url=\"https://www.opentopodata.org/#public-api\">domača "
"stran opentopodata.org</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, such a server lookup has to be triggered manually. It's also "
"possible to enable automated altitude lookups for all images dropped on the "
"map (which yields geographic coordinates but no elevation) and coordinates "
"entered manually."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je treba takšno iskanje strežnika sprožiti ročno. Prav tako je "
"mogoče omogočiti samodejno iskanje nadmorske višine za vse slike, ki so "
"spuščene na zemljevid (kar daje geografske koordinate, ne pa tudi nadmorske "
"višine) in ročno vnesene koordinate."

#. Tag: title
#: overview.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Making the data persistent"
msgstr "Izdelava obstojnih podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, the assigned coordinates can be saved. KGeoTag can either write "
"them to the images' Exif header (which will obviously alter the respective "
"files), to XMP sidecar files (leaving the original files untouched) or to "
"both. By default, a backup of each original file is created if it will be "
"changed during the write process."
msgstr ""
"Končno lahko dodeljene koordinate shranite. KGeoTag jih lahko zapiše v Exif "
"glavo slik (kar bo očitno spremenilo zadevne datoteke), v priklopne datoteke "
"XMP (pri čemer pusti izvirne datoteke nedotaknjene) ali v oboje. Privzeto se "
"ustvari varnostna kopija vsake izvirne datoteke, če bo spremenjena med "
"postopkom pisanja."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This way, the geodata assignment is made persistent and also accessible for "
"other geodata-aware applications (like &eg; <ulink url=\"https://www."
"kphotoalbum.org/\">KPhotoAlbum</ulink>)."
msgstr ""
"Na ta način je dodelitev geopodatkov obstojna in dostopna tudi drugim "
"aplikacijam, ki poznajo geopodatke (kot je &eg; <ulink url=\"https://www."
"kphotoalbum.org/\">KPhotoAlbum</ulink>)."

#. Tag: para
#: overview.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a time drift has been identified and a deviation has been given, the "
"images' dates and times also can be fixed whilst saving."
msgstr ""
"Če je bil ugotovljen časovni zamik in je bilo podano odstopanje, je mogoče "
"med shranjevanjem popraviti tudi datume in ure slik."
